 25  /-- A lax monoidal functor is a functor `F : C ⥤ D` between monoidal categories, equipped with morphisms
 26      `ε : 𝟙 _D ⟶ F.obj (𝟙_ C)` and `μ X Y : F.obj X ⊗ F.obj Y ⟶ F.obj (X ⊗ Y)`, satisfying the
 27      the appropriate coherences. -/
 28  structure lax_monoidal_functor extends C ⥤ D :=
 29  -- unit morphism
 30  (ε               : 𝟙_ D ⟶ obj (𝟙_ C))
 31  -- tensorator
 32  (μ                : Π X Y : C, (obj X) ⊗ (obj Y) ⟶ obj (X ⊗ Y))
 33  (μ_natural'       : ∀ {X Y X' Y' : C}
 34    (f : X ⟶ Y) (g : X' ⟶ Y'),
 35    ((map f) ⊗ (map g)) ≫ μ Y Y' = μ X X' ≫ map (f ⊗ g)
 36    . obviously)
 37  -- associativity of the tensorator
 38  (associativity'   : ∀ (X Y Z : C),
 39      (μ X Y ⊗ 𝟙 (obj Z)) ≫ μ (X ⊗ Y) Z ≫ map (α_ X Y Z).hom
 40    = (α_ (obj X) (obj Y) (obj Z)).hom ≫ (𝟙 (obj X) ⊗ μ Y Z) ≫ μ X (Y ⊗ Z)
 41    . obviously)
 42  -- unitality
 43  (left_unitality'  : ∀ X : C,
 44      (λ_ (obj X)).hom
 45    = (ε ⊗ 𝟙 (obj X)) ≫ μ (𝟙_ C) X ≫ map (λ_ X).hom
 46    . obviously)
 47  (right_unitality' : ∀ X : C,
id                             ┴
typ                            ┴
 48      (ρ_ (obj X)).hom
id        └┘  └─┘ ┴  └─┘
src       └┘         └─┘
typ       └┘  └─┘ ┴  └─┘
 49    = (𝟙 (obj X) ⊗ ε) ≫ μ X (𝟙_ C) ≫ map (ρ_ X).hom
id     ┴  ┴  └─┘ ┴  ┴ ┴  ┴ ┴ ┴  └┘ ┴  ┴ └─┘  └┘ ┴ └─┘
src    ┴  ┴         ┴    ┴      └┘    ┴      └┘   └─┘
typ    ┴  ┴  └─┘ ┴  ┴ ┴  ┴ ┴ ┴  └┘ ┴  ┴ └─┘  └┘ ┴ └─┘
 50    . obviously)
